#: ../../B/buried-treasure.rst:5
msgid "buried treasure"
msgstr "buried treasure"

#: ../../B/buried-treasure.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/buried-treasure.rst:9
msgid ""
"A surprising piece of code found in some program. While usually not wrong, "
"it tends to vary from :ref:`crufty` to :ref:`bletcherous`\\, and has lain "
"undiscovered only because it was functionally correct, however horrible it "
"is. Used sarcastically, because what is found is anything *but* treasure. "
"Buried treasure almost always needs to be dug up and removed. \"I just found"
" that the scheduler sorts its queue using :ref:`bubble-sort`\\! Buried "
"treasure!\""
msgstr ""
"あるプログラムの中で見つかる、驚くべきコードの一片。たいてい間違ってはいないが、\\ :ref:`crufty`\\ から\\ "
":ref:`bletcherous`\\ "
"まで様々で、どれほどひどくとも機能的には正しかったために、ただ発見されずに横たわっていた、というもの。皮肉を込めて使う。なぜなら、見つかるものは宝物などでは\\"
" *まったく*\\ ないからだ。buried treasureはほぼ常に掘り出して取り除く必要がある。「スケジューラがキューを\\ "
":ref:`bubble-sort`\\ でソートしているのを今見つけた! buried treasureだ!」"
